The paper deals with the problem of lineage tracing, which involves segmenting and tracking living cells in microscopy images. This problem is commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) communities. The authors also propose a mathematical abstraction of the problem, which involves defining a lineage forest of cells, which is a problem that falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.DM, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
